<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Service Agreement and Membership Contract</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
            font-size: 12px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #000;
            padding: 60px 80px;
            background: white;
        }

        .header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #000;
            padding-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .document-title {
            font-size: 24pt;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 15px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .date {
            text-align: right;
            font-style: italic;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            color: #555;
        }

        .info-box {
            background: #f8f8f8;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            padding: 25px;
            margin: 30px 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .info-box h3 {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            font-size: 14px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding-bottom: 5px;
        }

        .info-row {
            display: flex;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .info-label {
            font-weight: bold;
            width: 200px;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .info-value {
            flex: 1;
        }

        .section {
            margin: 25px 0;
        }

        .section-title {
            font-size: 13px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .section-content {
            text-align: justify;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        ul {
            margin-left: 40px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }

        strong {
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .form-row {
            margin-top: 30px;
            page-break-inside: avoid;
        }

        .form-label {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }

        .form-line {
            border-bottom: 1px solid #000;
            min-height: 40px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .signature-section {
            margin-top: 40px;
            page-break-inside: avoid;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="header">
        <div class="document-title">SERVICE AGREEMENT & MEMBERSHIP CONTRACT</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Date -->
    <div class="date">Effective Date: {{date}}</div>

    <!-- Business Information Box -->
    <div class="info-box">
        <h3>Provider Information</h3>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Business Name:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{BusinessName}}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Legal Entity:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{LegalEntityName}}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Address:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{BusinessAddress}}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Email:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{Email}}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Phone:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{Phone}}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Services Offered:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{Services}}</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-content">
            This Service Agreement and Membership Contract ("Agreement") is entered into between
            <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong> ("Provider," "we," "us," or "our") and the individual signing below
            ("Member," "you," or "your").
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            By signing this Agreement or purchasing a membership, you agree to be bound by the terms and conditions set
            forth below.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 1 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">1. SERVICES PROVIDED</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong> provides wellness and fitness services, including but not limited to:
            {{Services}}, and related activities (collectively, the "Services").
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            The specific services available to you will depend on your membership type, package purchased, or booking
            selections. We reserve the right to modify, add, or discontinue any Services at our discretion with reasonable
            notice.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 2 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">2. MEMBERSHIP TYPES AND TERMS</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We offer various membership options, which may include:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Monthly Membership:</strong> Automatically renews each month until canceled</li>
            <li><strong>Prepaid Packages:</strong> Fixed number of classes or sessions valid for a specified period</li>
            <li><strong>Annual Membership:</strong> 12-month commitment with discounted rates</li>
            <li><strong>Drop-In/Single Classes:</strong> Pay-per-session without ongoing commitment</li>
            <li><strong>Special Promotions:</strong> Limited-time offers with specific terms</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="section-content">
            The specific terms, duration, pricing, and benefits of your membership will be outlined in your purchase
            confirmation or membership agreement.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 3 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">3. PAYMENT TERMS</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>A. Pricing and Fees</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Membership fees, class prices, and package rates are subject to change with 30 days' notice. Current members
            will be notified of price changes via email.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>B. Payment Methods</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We accept payment via credit card, debit card, bank transfer, or other methods specified at the time of
            purchase. By providing payment information, you authorize us to charge the agreed-upon fees.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>C. Recurring Payments</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Monthly and annual memberships will automatically renew and your payment method will be charged on the renewal
            date unless you cancel prior to that date. It is your responsibility to keep your payment information current.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>D. Failed Payments</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            If a payment fails, we may suspend your membership until payment is received. A failed payment fee may apply.
            If payment is not received within 14 days, your membership may be terminated.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>E. Late Fees</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Late fees may apply for overdue balances. We reserve the right to send unpaid accounts to collections.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 4 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">4. CANCELLATION AND REFUND POLICY</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>A. Monthly Memberships</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            You may cancel your monthly membership at any time by providing written notice (email acceptable) at least 7
            days before your next billing date. Cancellations received after this period will take effect the following
            billing cycle. No refunds will be provided for partial months.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>B. Prepaid Packages and Annual Memberships</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Prepaid packages and annual memberships are generally non-refundable. Exceptions may be made for medical
            reasons (with doctor's note), relocation more than 50 miles away, or other extenuating circumstances at our
            sole discretion.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>C. Class Cancellations</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            If we cancel a class or service, you will receive a credit, makeup session, or refund as appropriate. We are
            not responsible for cancellations due to weather, emergencies, or circumstances beyond our control.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 5 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">5. CLASS BOOKING AND ATTENDANCE</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>A. Reservations</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Classes may require advance booking. We recommend booking early as space is limited. No-shows may result in
            loss of class credit.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>B. Late Arrivals</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Arriving more than 10 minutes late may result in being turned away to avoid disrupting the class. Late arrivals
            will still be charged or lose a class credit.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>C. Cancellation Policy</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            You must cancel your class reservation at least 12 hours in advance to avoid losing your class credit.
            Frequent late cancellations or no-shows may result in membership suspension or termination.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 6 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">6. MEMBER RESPONSIBILITIES</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            As a Member, you agree to:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li>Consult with a physician before beginning any fitness program and disclose any medical conditions or
                injuries;</li>
            <li>Follow all instructions from instructors and staff;</li>
            <li>Use equipment and facilities safely and as intended;</li>
            <li>Respect other members, instructors, and staff;</li>
            <li>Arrive on time and prepared for classes;</li>
            <li>Maintain personal hygiene and wear appropriate attire;</li>
            <li>Keep personal belongings secure (we are not responsible for lost or stolen items);</li>
            <li>Notify us immediately of any changes to your contact or payment information;</li>
            <li>Comply with all studio policies, rules, and code of conduct.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 7 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">7. ASSUMPTION OF RISK AND WAIVER</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            You acknowledge that participation in fitness and wellness activities involves inherent risks, including the
            risk of injury or death. By signing this Agreement, you assume all such risks and waive any claims against
            <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong>, its owners, employees, instructors, and agents for injuries or damages
            arising from your participation.
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            This waiver includes claims for negligence, premises liability, or any other legal theory. You agree to
            indemnify and hold harmless <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong> from any third-party claims arising from your
            actions.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 8 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">8. CODE OF CONDUCT</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We are committed to maintaining a safe, welcoming, and respectful environment. Unacceptable behavior includes:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li>Harassment, discrimination, or bullying of any kind;</li>
            <li>Disruptive, rude, or aggressive behavior;</li>
            <li>Use of drugs or alcohol on premises;</li>
            <li>Theft, vandalism, or damage to property;</li>
            <li>Unauthorized filming, photography, or recording;</li>
            <li>Solicitation or promotion of outside businesses without permission.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="section-content">
            Violation of our code of conduct may result in immediate membership termination without refund.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 9 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">9. GUEST POLICY</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Members may bring guests subject to our guest policy. Guests must sign a waiver and pay applicable fees.
            Members are responsible for their guests' behavior and compliance with studio policies.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 10 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">10. SUSPENSION AND TERMINATION</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your membership for:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li>Violation of this Agreement or studio policies;</li>
            <li>Non-payment of fees;</li>
            <li>Disruptive or inappropriate behavior;</li>
            <li>Providing false information;</li>
            <li>Any reason at our sole discretion.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="section-content">
            Termination due to misconduct will result in forfeiture of all remaining classes, credits, and fees paid.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 11 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">11. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong> shall not be liable for any
            indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of our Services, even if we
            have been advised of the possibility of such damages.
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid for your membership or services in the 6 months prior
            to the claim.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 12 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">12. GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of <strong>{{Jurisdiction}}</strong>. Any disputes
            shall be resolved through binding arbitration or in the courts of <strong>{{Jurisdiction}}</strong>.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 13 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">13. ENTIRE AGREEMENT</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            This Agreement, together with our policies and waivers, constitutes the entire agreement between you and
            <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong> and supersedes all prior agreements.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Acknowledgement -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">ACKNOWLEDGEMENT</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            By signing below, I acknowledge that I have read, understood, and agree to be bound by this Service Agreement
            and Membership Contract.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Signature Section -->
    <div class="signature-section">
        <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-label">Member Name (Print):</div>
            <div class="form-line"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-label">Signature:</div>
            <div class="form-line"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-label">Date:</div>
            <div class="form-line"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-label">Email:</div>
            <div class="form-line"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-label">Phone:</div>
            <div class="form-line"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-label">Membership Type:</div>
            <div class="form-line"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>

</html>